The paper deals with the problem of matching a query string to a directed graph, which has applications in data mining and computational biology. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper presents results on the fixed-parameter tractability of the problem, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
